    
    👤 1. EXPLAINING TO A USER (NO TECHNICAL TERMS)

    🧠 What is happening in my app?

    When a user uses your system:

    👉 Step 1: Frontend (what the user sees)
            .The user types:
                .Event name
                .Organizer
                .Venue
                .Capacity
            .Then clicks “Add Event”
            👉 At this moment:
                    The website collects that information

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    👉 Step 2: Sending data to the server
        
        .The app sends that information to the backend (server)

    👉 Think of it like:

        “Hey server, please save this new event”

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    👉 Step 3: Backend (server work)
            .The server receives the data
            .It splits it into:
                .Organizer
                .Venue
                .Event

    👉 Then:

        .Saves each one in the database
        .Links them together

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    👉 Step 4: Database (storage)

        The database stores:
            .Organizer (e.g. RBA)
            .Venue (e.g. Camp Kigali, capacity 100)
            .Event (e.g. Concert → linked to organizer & venue)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    👉 Step 5: Getting data back

        .The frontend asks:

            “Give me all events”

        .The backend responds with:
            .Event name
            .Organizer name
            .Venue name

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    👉 Step 6: Display
        .The frontend shows everything in the table

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------        

    🎯 SIMPLE SUMMARY (USER LEVEL)

    👉 “When you add an event, the system sends your data to a server, 
        which saves it in a database and connects everything properly. 
        Then it sends the organized data back to be displayed on the screen.”

